        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 2:42PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 241 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Marion Wytheville, or near Rural Retreat, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Wytheville...
Rural Retreat...
Max Meadows...
Speedwell...
Marion Wytheville...
Fort Chiswell...
and Cripple Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

Additional statements will be issued as conditions warrant.</instruction>
